Privacy Policy
EEA Residents here.
This Privacy Policy is designed by United Marketing Technologies, Inc. to assist you in understanding how we collect, use, disclose and/or process the information you provide to us when you play our Mobile Game App, “CocoPPa Play”, and receive other services related to the App.
1. Information you provide to us
a. email address
b. country/region
c. terminal identifier（MAC Address, Advertisement ID provided by OS）
2. How we use information we collect
(1) email address
To respond to your inquiry and support your Data Transfer.
(2) Your country/region, terminal identifier（MAC Address, Advertisement ID provided by OS）
To view statistics regarding your usage of our services, prevent our service from being used against our Terms of service, and survey and analyze the data to improve our service.
3. We do not disclose or supply your information to third party without your consent except as permitted by law.
4. You can delete your account at any time. When you delete your account, all the information related to your account will be deleted permanently.
"5. We create statistics based on the information provided by you in only the form of
non-personally identifiable information. This information is to be used statistically to control the information displayed in the App as well as to provide you better services."
"6. Some of our services may include cookies and similar technologies. We use this kind of information as one of our statistical marketing information to provide you more personally customized information/services. Please be note that cookies do not include personal information.
							In addition, we may use WEB advertisement network cookies in order to provide you customized information. This is only to be used in order to segment your action history and never be used to acquire your personal information nor to connect to your registered information."
7. Since our service is not directed to children under 13, we do not knowingly collect personal information from them. In case we happened to collect personal information from child under 13 without parental consent, we will take the appropriate measures to delete the information.
"8. Module for collecting information
							In order to provide our service for free, the advertising companies listed below will automatically collect your information with the purpose of distributing advertisements. Please go visit each company’s webpages to view the types of information they collect, the purposes they collect information, and their third party disclosure policies."
--------------------
a. Name of service: Google Analytics
Supplier: Google
Type of information to collect: Unique ID(UUID) generated in the SDK, device information
Purpose: To measure the number of service users and withdrawal timing
Provision to third parties: None
https://policies.google.com/privacy
--------------------
b. Name of service: AppsFlyer
Supplier: AppsFlyer
Type of information to collect: Usage history of this application, including application information, device ID, device information, communication information, event information, and application operation information (not including information that identifies individuals)
Purpose: To analyze user behavior and measure the effectiveness of advertisements
https://www.appsflyer.com/legal/services-privacy-policy/
--------------------
c. Name of service: Firebase
Supplier: Google
Type of information to collect: Unique ID(UUID) generated in the SDK, device information
Purpose: Send push notifications, analyze user behavior
Provision to third parties: None
https://policies.google.com/privacy
--------------------
d. Name of service： AdStir
Supplier： UNITED Marketing Technologies, Inc.
Type of the information to collect： Creation of [Android]UIID [iOS]IDFA
Purpose： User targeting concerning advertisement
Provision to third parties： Yes （To each DSP）
https://mt.united.jp/rule.html
9. We reserve the right to modify or amend this Privacy Policy at any time. All the changes will be effective as soon as it be displayed in the App.
10. If you wish to stop your information to get collected by the App, please uninstall the App.
11. Should you have any queries or require any further information, please contact us by email below.
